<p>Grsecurity has been developed and maintained in our free time for the past 14 years.  Please <a href="contribute.php">contribute</a> toward the project's continued research and development in Linux security.  Businesses are encouraged to purchase an annual <a href='/business_support.php'>support contract</a> for direct access to grsecurity developers in the event of any deployment issues.<br /><br />Grsecurity and gradm are licensed under the <a href='https://www.gnu.org'>GNU</a> <a href='https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0-standalone.html'>GPL version 2</a> only.<br /><strong>Know your rights!</strong>  As a customer of any product that uses grsecurity in binary form, you are entitled to the complete corresponding source code.  Companies who do not ship the complete corresponding source code alongside distributed binaries must provide you with a written offer for the source code transferrable to any other person and valid for three years.  Please report any violations of our GPL license to spender@grsecurity.net.<br /><br />For instructions on how to compile a grsecurity-enabled kernel, see the <a href="https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Grsecurity/Configuring_and_Installing_grsecurity">documentation</a>.</p>
